[293.283232, "o", "                                           \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[7;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mWhy it's empty\u001b[0m                                                                                          \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[8;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36mpython3 -m http.server\u001b[0m only writes a line each time it \u001b[1;97mserves a request\u001b[0m (e.g. \u001b[36m127.0.0.1 - - [..] \"GET /\u001b[0m \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[9;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36mHTTP/1.1\" 200 -\u001b[0m). No request log lines means \u001b[1;97mno one has hit the server yet\u001b[0m.                             \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[10;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                         \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[11;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mTo make it print something\u001b[0m                                                                              \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[12;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m   • Open \u001b[1;97mhttp://localhost:8000/\u001b[0m in a browser, or                                                        \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\u001b[13;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m   • \u001b[36mcurl http://l"]
